The White House has announced the appointment of Suzy George as the new Deputy Assistant to the President, Executive Secretary of the National Security Council, and Chief of Staff of the National Security Council staff. She will be succeeding Brian McKeon, who is leaving the White House to become the Principal Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Policy at the Department of Defense. Susan E. Rice, the National Security Adviser, praised George's extensive foreign policy, government, and management experience, gained from her service at the Department of State and her role as a principal at the Albright Stonebridge Group LLC. George previously served as the Deputy Chief of Staff in the Department of State from 1997-2001. She holds a BA from Mount Holyoke College and a JD from the George Washington University Law School.